from word_freq import WordAnalyzer

IELTS = WordAnalyzer('The bar chart illustrates the regularity of eating at fast food restaurants in different years 2003,2006,2013 among people in the USA.Overall, The chart shows the frequency of dining at restaurants in three different years such as - 2003,2006,2013. The bar chart showcases the rise of dining once a week at approximately 33% in 2006 and with the same rate going once or twice a month in 2013. Dining every day in 2003 saw the lowest rate with a small positive difference with 2003.Starting with the lowest percentage in every category was every day. every day in 2003 a percentage of 4 used to have fast food and the same percentage in both 2006,2013 well over 3%. Eating several times the rate rose significantly in all the years where 2006 with 20%, 17% in 2003, 16% in 2013. Once in a week and once or twice a month dining at fast food restaurant showed the most significant rise - at around 31% in 2003, 33% in 2006 and 28% in 2006 people used to go dining once in a week and eating once or twice a month in 2003 was 30%, 25% in 2006 and 33% in 2013. The frequency of eating a few times a year drops noticeably throughout all three years, in 2003 it dropped to 13% and on the other hand 2006,2013 dropped to the similar rate of 15%. Never going to dine at fast food restaurants was 5% in 2003 and it decreased even more in 2006 and 2013 at 4%.In summary, people in the USA eat less fast food on a daily basis but it increases to highest dramatically as it goes to week and month where people eat several times. But the percentage decreases on a yearly basis. A good amount of people have never dined at fast food restaurants in all three years.')
IELTS.report()